Package: juliaready
Title: Robust Julia Setup for R Packages
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Sebastian", "Funk", , "sebastian.funk@lshtm.ac.uk",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-2842-3406"))
Description: Helper utilities for R packages that wrap a Julia simulation
    engine via JuliaCall. Provides a small, opinionated API for finding
    the right Julia binary, installing and precompiling Julia packages
    via subprocess (avoiding known JuliaCall segfaults on stale caches),
    loading '.jl' bridge files in a world-age-safe way, and managing
    lazy initialisation. Captures patterns refined across several
    R-with-Julia-backend packages so the next one does not have to
    rediscover them.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/sbfnk/juliaready
BugReports: https://github.com/sbfnk/juliaready/issues
